ICS 1C Labs, Teams, and Quiz 1

  • To: Multiple recipients of list <ics1c@UCI.EDU>
  • Subject: ICS 1C Labs, Teams, and Quiz 1
  • From: ICS 1C Instructional Staff <ics1c@ics.uci.edu>
  • Date: Wed, 18 Jan 1995 07:30:40 -0800 
This Friday, Jan 20, only, ICS 1C will have lab hours 7:30-11a.m.
to compensate for the fact that the lab was not available on Monday.

By noon on Friday, Jan 20, each team should e-mail to ics1c@ics.uci.edu
a list of the names and e-mail addresses of all members of the team
in the form:
   First_Name_1 Last_Name_1 <e-mail_address_1@ea.oac.uci.edu>
   First_Name_2 Last_Name_2 <e-mail_address_2@ea.oac.uci.edu>
   First_Name_3 Last_Name_3 <e-mail_address_3@ea.oac.uci.edu>
   First_Name_4 Last_Name_4 <e-mail_address_4@ea.oac.uci.edu>
   ...
Also, please enclose at the end of this message which 2 of the 8
Lab times (see below) team members can be in the lab together.
Lab times:
    Monday 7:30-11 a.m.:  
      "Mon Early" = Starting Before 8; "Mon Late" = Starting after 9
    Tuesday 9-11 a.m. = "Tues Early"; Tuesday 3-5 p.m. = "Tues Late"
    Wednesday 7:30-11 a.m.:  
      "Wed Early" = Starting Before 8; "Wed Late" = Starting after 9
    Thursday 9-11 a.m. = "Thurs Early"; Thursday 5-6 p.m. = "Thurs Late"

Monday, 23 January, Quiz 1:
   2 Articles by V. Bush and by T. Berners-Lee and cohorts
   Text, Parts 1 and 2
   Materials covered in class meetings and lab exercises through 20 Jan.

-- sdf
Stephen Franklin
ICS 1C Instructor
